The paper proposes a framework for modeling sequential data coming from a set of entities connected in a graph, which involves machine learning techniques such as hidden Markov models and mixture models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the proposed method and its applications.
